# Memory Bank Protocol

The memory bank is a persistent, cross-referenced knowledge graph maintained in a **separate repository**:

**→ https://github.com/bmaio-redhat/kubevirt-memory**

Do **not** store memory bank files in this repository. All agents must read from and contribute to the external repo.

## How to Access

- **Local path**: `/home/bmaio/Developer/Projects/kubevirt-memory`
- **Remote**: https://github.com/bmaio-redhat/kubevirt-memory

Read and write files directly at the local path. Commit and push to `main` in the external repo when contributing new nodes.

## Three Checkpoints (ALL Personas)

### 1. Before Work — Read

At the start of a task, consult the external memory bank:
1. Read `index.md` to see what nodes exist
2. Read nodes relevant to the current task (features, tickets, gotchas, flaky tests)
3. Use what you find — don't rediscover what a previous session already learned

### 2. During Work — Note

Track decisions, gotchas, framework changes, and coverage gaps as you work.

### 3. After Work — Write and Prune

Contribute findings back to the external repo:
- Create or update nodes in the appropriate directory
- Prune stale entries found during reads
- Never add cluster credentials, tokens, passwords, or `.env` values
